data.name: GFFFORMATTER_DESCRIPTION
data.value: Writes an ISequence to a particular location, usually a file. The output is formatted according to the GFF file format. A method is also provided for quickly accessing the content in string form for applications that do not need to first write to file.

data.name: GFFPARSER_DESCRIPTION
data.value: A GffParser reads from a source of text that is formatted according to the GFF flat file specification, and converts the data to in-memory ISequence objects. For advanced users, the ability to select an encoding for the internal memory representation is provided. There is also a default encoding for each alphabet that may be encountered.

data.name: GFF_FILEEXTENSION
data.value: .gff

data.name: GFF_NAME
data.value: GFF
